The paper deals with the task of click-through rate (CTR) prediction in online display advertising systems using deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development and application of algorithms that enable computers to learn from data. The paper also involves the use of image features, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision), which deals with the analysis and understanding of digital images and videos. Additionally, the paper involves the use of contextual features, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the retrieval of information from large collections of data. The paper also involves the use of natural language processing techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the study of computational aspects of natural language. Finally, the paper involves the use of multimedia data, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), which deals with the processing, analysis, and retrieval of multimedia data.
